fig.basic
Class T2VMap<S,T,V>

java.lang.Object
  fig.basic.AbstractT2Map
      fig.basic.T2VMap<S,T,V>
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Iterable<Map.Entry<S,TVMap<T,V>>>
public class T2VMap<S,T,V>
extends AbstractT2Map
implements Iterable<Map.Entry<S,TVMap<T,V>>>, Serializable

Maps (object, object) pairs to objects. Based on T2VMap. It's useful when the number of second objects for a fixed first string is small. Most of the operations in this class parallel that of T2VMap, but just applied to two keys. The implementation is essentially dispatching down to T2VMap. Typical usage: conditional probability table.
